title: Republican infighting paralyzes the House as some call a shutdown inevitable
description: Republican divisions have paralyzed the House as GOP leaders abandoned a vote to avert a government shutdown at the end of the month.

title: Fighting ‘the beast’: Inside the desperate quest to save Lahaina
description: Maui’s firefighters faced an unprecedented challenge in the Lahaina wildfire: deadly wind-whipped flames they couldn’t defeat. “We lost to the beast,” one said.

title: Zelenskyy implores world leaders to stick with fight against Russia
description: Ukraine President Volodymyr Zelenskyy appeared somber and, at times, angry in a blistering address to the U.N. General Assembly in Manhattan on Tuesday.

title: Despite recent uptick, Covid leveling off in some areas of the country, wastewater testing shows
description: The spike in Covid cases may be plateauing, according to wastewater testing data. But experts warn the virus still poses a threat and getting the vaccine is critical.

title: Fentanyl was stored on top of playmats at Bronx day care where baby fell ill and later died
description: The owner of the New York City day care center where a 1-year-old boy fell ill and later died, and three other kids got sick from apparent opioid exposure, has been hit with federal drug conspiracy charges.

title: DOJ charges Ray Epps, subject of Tucker Carlson's Jan. 6 conspiracy theories
description: Ray Epps, a Jan. 6 participant who was the subject of conspiracy theories, was charged in connection with the Capitol attack on Tuesday.

title: Northern lights put on a show across parts of Canada and U.S.
description: Dazzling displays of the northern lights wowed skywatchers across parts of Canada and the United States on Monday night, after a powerful eruption from the sun supercharged the aurora borealis.

title: FTX sues founder Sam Bankman-Fried’s parents
description: Bankrupt crypto exchange FTX on Monday sued the parents of founder Sam Bankman-Fried, saying that Stanford professors Joseph Bankman and Barbara Fried used the company to enrich themselves at the expense of FTX’s customers.

title: Trial to start in the death of Elijah McClain, a Black man injected with ketamine by EMT during police chokehold
description: The trial of two police officers charged in the death of Elijah McClain, a Black man placed in a chokehold and injected with ketamine is set to begin this week.

title: Moscow court declines to consider appeal by U.S. reporter Evan Gershkovich
description: A Moscow court on Tuesday declined to consider the latest appeal by U.S. reporter Evan Gershkovich against his pre-trial detention, nearly six months after his arrest on spying charges that he denies.

title: Microsoft's Xbox plans revealed in emails tied to FTC case
description: A huge collection of purported Xbox files related to the Federal Trade Commission’s case against Microsoft have been published online.

title: Cleveland Browns running back Nick Chubb out for season after knee injury
description: Cleveland Browns’ star running back Nick Chubb will likely be out for the season after he was carted off the field during a game against the Pittsburgh Steelers on Monday night after a severe knee injury.

title: Five Americans freed from Iran arrive back in the U.S. after prisoner swap
description: Five Americans who were released after being wrongfully imprisoned in Iran for years have arrived back on U.S. soil after a prisoner swap.

title: Search for missing fighter jet turns to recovery as officials probe what happened in 'mishap'
description: The search for a missing F-35 stealth fighter jet turned to a recovery mission Tuesday after authorities located a debris field in South Carolina, capping an unusual saga that drew global attention.

title: Canada accuses India of an assassination on its soil, leading both countries to expel diplomats
description: India rejected as “absurd” an accusation that it was behind the killing in Canada of Sikh activist Hardeep Singh Nijjar, as both countries expelled diplomats.

title: YouTube blocks Russell Brand from making money off his channel after sexual assault allegations
description: YouTube has blocked Russell Brand from making money off its platform in the wake of rape and sexual assault allegations against the comedian and actor.

title: ‘I plan to wear a bikini’: Senate Republicans mock changes to dress code
description: The new dress code will allow Sen. John Fetterman to wear his trademark casual attire like hoodies and shorts on the Senate floor.

title: UAW will strike more plants if ‘serious progress’ isn’t made by noon Friday
description: The United Auto Workers will announce strikes at more General Motors, Ford Motor and Stellantis plants if the sides don’t make “serious progress” in negotiations by noon ET Friday.
